<title>Programming Power Font</title>
<subtitle>...for Lisp</subtitle>
<excerpt/>
<body><![CDATA[<p>I've always liked the <strong>Proggy</strong> font, the bold punctuation really makes things stand out especially, especially if you program in Lisp where parens aren't just syntactic sugar, they represent functions and power.<br />
<br />
So after getting my mits on the <strong>Inconsolata</strong> font, I did some modifications to create a version with bold punctuation.&nbsp; It's especially helpful in environments that don't offer syntax coloration.<br />
<br />
An example:</p>
<p><img alt="Inconsolata Bold Punct example" src="https://github.com/heow/inconsolata-boldpunct/raw/master/screenshot.png" /><br />
<br />
<a href="https://github.com/heow/inconsolata-boldpunct/raw/master/Inconsolata-BoldPunct.ttf">Grab the TTF here.</a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
